{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"body":"## Content fix SHIPPED + validated\n**T10 infra overlay gains one `endpoint_access_contract` bullet** (rubric + checklist): every\nnetwork-reachable service a plan STANDS UP must state human/admin auth (named mechanism OR\njustified no-auth); machine creds (deploy keys/tokens/SSM) do NOT satisfy it. Grounded in\ndeny-by-default (OWASP C5) + trust-boundary reachability (STRIDE/ASVS 1.4.1) + ASVS 1.1.4.\nT10 chosen because it fires ONLY on infra intent ⇒ inherently FP-safe on local work.\n\n### Validation on the Gerrit epic d251 (the specific ask)\nHarness = Pass-1 finder, REAL shipped criterion (no override):\n- **OLD** (T5c, type-gated to task): never ran on the epic (applies(T5c,epic)=False); forced to run,\n  4 samples flagged only encryption/token — the missing Gerrit auth was NOT flagged. ✓ (1) old did not flag.\n- **NEW** (T10 endpoint_access_contract): flagged the missing human/admin auth in **6/6** runs,\n  correctly naming auth.type=DEVELOPMENT_BECOME_ANY_ACCOUNT + the 0.0.0.0/0 exposure. ✓ (2) new flags.\n- **Negatives** (local, no-network, security-FLAVORED): 8a1c (gate-signing) 0 findings; 4702\n  (attestations) 0 findings — **0/4 false positives**.\n\n591 unit tests pass; routing parity gate OK; make lint clean; prompt-index in sync."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1782890719257440001,"uuid":"02d649b2-1592-4d25-ae00-996d76bd0273"}